RISING star, Ebosetale Gideon Solomon aka Yung Bos has won the award for ‘Best Collaboration’ at the 8th edition of the Top Naija Music Awards for 2021. The award, which had its first edition in 2013, rewards emerging artistic talents and fast-rising music stars in the Nigerian music and entertainment industry. Yung Bos, who many considered a novice in the music industry after being signed to Jamika Entertainment in 2021, surprised all as he picked up the award with his career debut, ‘Smile’ featuring fellow label mate Sultan a.k.a Afroboy. Sultan would also go on to win the award for ‘Next Rated’ at the event while his record label Jamika Entertainment also won ‘Best Music Label.’   Dice releases debut EP, 48 Hours In The Motherland     UNLIMITED LA: My encounter with police during Sean…     Side chicks, major reason most men are still married –…   Read Also: Marginal field: 33 awardees fail to pay signature bonuses - Advertisement - It was all smiles for Yung Bos whose manager, Stanley Ihensekhien, also won the award for ‘Entertainment Entrepreneur’ and his producer Dave ‘Dexterity’ Achina won the award for ‘Best Music Producer’. The young singer was short of words as he expressed his delight and gratitude for winning his first award. “I feel so blessed to have won this in my first year with my first release, I wouldn’t take this for granted and I will continue to give my best to prove this wasn’t a fluke,” he said. Yung Bos is currently working on his first studio album and plans to release it in 2022.